WEBVTT

00:05.458 --> 00:09.250
♪ [OMINOUS TV MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

00:16.000 --> 00:17.291
[SCREAMS]

00:17.792 --> 00:20.583
Joey: [ON TV, GROANS]

00:30.167 --> 00:31.208
You know, this sucks a lot

00:31.208 --> 00:32.667
more than I remembered it.

00:33.667 --> 00:35.291
Dawson, need I remind you that.

00:35.291 --> 00:37.000
Sea Creature from the Deep

00:37.000 --> 00:38.875
won the jurors prize in the
junior division

00:38.875 --> 00:40.125
at the Boston film festival,

00:40.125 --> 00:42.042
for which you were rewarded

00:42.042 --> 00:43.834
the princely sum of $2,500.

00:43.834 --> 00:45.125
Yeah, right. Which I then
proceeded

00:45.125 --> 00:46.125
to waste on my next endeavor,

00:46.125 --> 00:47.084
which was entitled...

00:47.084 --> 00:48.083
What was it called again?

00:48.083 --> 00:50.250
Ah, that's right.
Self-indulgentpiece of crap.

00:50.250 --> 00:52.333
Blah, blah, blah, blah.

00:55.084 --> 00:56.417
Seriously, though, Jo. How did
we get here?

00:56.417 --> 00:57.708
I mean, it...

00:58.708 --> 00:59.500
It feels like one second

00:59.500 --> 01:01.125
we're sitting here watching
E.T.,

01:01.125 --> 01:02.667
wondering what 10th grade is
gonna be like,

01:02.667 --> 01:03.667
and the next...

01:05.125 --> 01:06.291
We're leaving for college.

01:08.959 --> 01:11.125
Well, some of us are going
sooner than others.

01:11.917 --> 01:13.167
I mean, I have the entire summer

01:13.167 --> 01:14.333
to process my crippling anxiety,

01:14.667 --> 01:17.834
but, uh, you on the other
hand...

01:17.834 --> 01:19.250
Day after tomorrow.

01:22.041 --> 01:23.834
My college career begins the
day after tomorrow.

01:23.834 --> 01:24.834
You know, I'm starting to think

01:24.834 --> 01:25.750
this whole summer program

01:25.750 --> 01:26.750
was not such a good idea.

01:27.000 --> 01:29.750
Dawson, you have to focus on
the good.

01:30.750 --> 01:32.041
I mean, you got in, and not

01:32.041 --> 01:33.291
only do they want you,

01:33.291 --> 01:35.667
but they want you early. That's
huge.

01:37.166 --> 01:39.166
You might want to consider
packing, however.

01:39.708 --> 01:40.583
When you're in the kind of

01:40.583 --> 01:41.542
denial I'm in right now,

01:41.542 --> 01:43.291
there's just no room for
packing.

01:46.083 --> 01:47.083
Ok.

01:57.792 --> 01:58.875
Have you heard from him?

01:59.083 --> 02:00.208
No. The sea creature from the
deep

02:00.208 --> 02:01.208
remains incommunicado.

02:01.625 --> 02:02.625
I'm sorry.

02:03.083 --> 02:05.041
I'm sure once he's ready, he'll
call or write...

02:05.041 --> 02:06.041
Or something.

02:09.875 --> 02:10.875
I don't know.

02:11.542 --> 02:13.583
Do you ever feel utterly
incapable

02:13.583 --> 02:15.250
of sustaining a relationship?

02:17.209 --> 02:18.917
I think I'm in touch with that
emotion.

02:19.166 --> 02:21.166
I guess it's another in a
seemingly endless

02:21.166 --> 02:22.417
string of life lessons.

02:23.209 --> 02:24.167
Never get involved with a

02:24.167 --> 02:25.083
monster from beneath the sea,

02:25.083 --> 02:26.125
no matter how charming.

02:26.125 --> 02:28.959
It's... just not gonna work.

02:31.375 --> 02:33.250
I have to say that despite our
mutual misery,

02:33.250 --> 02:34.417
I've had a pretty decent time

02:34.417 --> 02:35.667
hanging out with you lately.

02:38.417 --> 02:39.417
Me, too.

02:44.000 --> 02:45.166
I wish it didn't have to end.

02:50.375 --> 02:52.583
Well, everything comes to an
end, Dawson.

02:52.583 --> 02:53.291
[SIGHS]

02:53.291 --> 02:54.959
Thank you, Sylvia Plath.

02:59.084 --> 03:00.417
I just wish it didn't, is all.

03:52.417 --> 03:54.125
Joey: I got the German flu.

03:54.458 --> 03:55.458
Dawson: The German flu?

03:55.458 --> 03:56.458
My aunt brought it over.

03:56.458 --> 03:57.708
Really?

03:57.959 --> 04:00.167
Dawson: In the meantime, the
movie's kind of...

04:00.167 --> 04:02.375
You know, black and white...

04:03.208 --> 04:04.792
Jen: Shouldn't we all be
looking for, like,

04:04.792 --> 04:06.167
summer jobs or something?

04:06.333 --> 04:08.042
Uh, some of us already have
those.

04:08.583 --> 04:09.750
Dawson: Yeah. Is it just me,

04:09.750 --> 04:10.792
or does that yacht club uniform

04:10.792 --> 04:12.208
keep getting sexier and sexier?

04:12.208 --> 04:13.208
Bite me.

04:13.208 --> 04:14.333
Dawson: Ha ha ha.

04:14.333 --> 04:15.583
You guys know there's always
work

04:15.583 --> 04:17.166
down at Leery's Fresh Fish.

04:17.166 --> 04:18.458
All: We know.

04:19.291 --> 04:21.125
Look. I got one.

04:22.083 --> 04:23.750
Yeah, I got one. You ready?

04:24.125 --> 04:25.125
Ok.

04:26.250 --> 04:29.209
Would you rather work two
straight shifts

04:29.333 --> 04:32.000
at the fresh fish house,
completely naked,

04:32.000 --> 04:35.166
or have sex once with principal
Peskin?

04:35.166 --> 04:36.917
[JEN AND JOEY GROAN]

04:36.917 --> 04:38.417
You got a better one, let me
know.

04:38.417 --> 04:39.500
Joey: Ok, I got one.

04:39.917 --> 04:40.792
Sex with Peskin,

04:40.792 --> 04:42.625
or having to spend your entire
freshmen year

04:42.625 --> 04:43.917
living with a roommate who

04:43.917 --> 04:45.041
smells really, really bad.

04:45.041 --> 04:46.166
Like, uh, like earth-hippie

04:46.166 --> 04:47.291
sworn-off-deodorant bad?

04:47.291 --> 04:49.166
No, like French-foreign-exchange
student bad.

04:49.166 --> 04:50.375
- Is he cute? - Jack.

04:50.375 --> 04:51.375
Kidding. I'm kidding.

04:51.375 --> 04:53.959
I got it. I got it. Ha ha.

04:53.959 --> 04:55.083
I've got a "would you rather"

04:55.083 --> 04:56.959
so brilliant in its
perversity...

04:56.959 --> 04:58.125
Oh, this better be good.

04:58.125 --> 04:59.583
Yeah, you know what? I wouldn't
preface

04:59.583 --> 05:00.375
your supposed brainstorms

05:00.375 --> 05:01.333
with the word "brilliant."

05:01.333 --> 05:02.875
I mean, it's just setting you
up for failure.

05:02.875 --> 05:04.667
Will you two harridans let the
man speak, please?

05:04.667 --> 05:05.583
Thank you. ok.

05:05.583 --> 05:07.208
Would you rather have sex with
Peskin

05:08.208 --> 05:10.125
or watch Peskin have sex with
Grams?

05:14.167 --> 05:17.083
Ok, ok, ok, ok. First of all,

05:17.083 --> 05:19.083
Grams would never have sex with
Peskin.

05:19.083 --> 05:20.417
And second of all, you win.

05:20.417 --> 05:21.166
Jen: That's disgusting.

05:21.166 --> 05:22.166
Joey: That is  disgusting.

05:22.792 --> 05:24.333
Mission accomplished. I now
leave town

05:24.333 --> 05:25.333
the reigning "would you"

05:25.333 --> 05:26.667
"rather" gross-out champion.

05:27.875 --> 05:29.291
Dawson: You guys know what time
it is?

05:29.291 --> 05:31.834
Yeah. It's, uh... it's almost
6:00.

05:31.834 --> 05:32.834
Shoot. Supposed to meet my dad

05:32.834 --> 05:34.000
like half an hour ago.

05:34.417 --> 05:35.250
Jen: Wait, are you still

05:35.250 --> 05:36.333
on for the movies tonight?

05:36.333 --> 05:38.000
Uh, yeah. Meet at my house at
7:00.

05:39.041 --> 05:40.834
- Bye. - Bye.

05:40.834 --> 05:42.333
- See ya. - Jack: See ya later.

05:46.875 --> 05:48.125
This baby does it all, Dawson.

05:48.417 --> 05:50.500
850 megahertz, p3 processor,

05:50.500 --> 05:52.667
128 megabytes of RAM,

05:53.209 --> 05:56.167
32-gig hard drive, DVD, 56k
modem.

05:56.708 --> 05:57.792
What more could you want?

05:58.208 --> 05:59.375
I don't know. A Mac, maybe?

05:59.375 --> 06:01.167
- What? - It's become obvious
to me

06:01.167 --> 06:02.166
that in life you're either a.

06:02.166 --> 06:03.375
Mac person or a PC person,

06:03.375 --> 06:04.625
and the choice defines you.

06:05.708 --> 06:07.792
Let me put it to you this way:
Beatles or Elvis?

06:07.792 --> 06:09.250
- Beatles. - See? Exactly. This
is no different.

06:09.250 --> 06:10.458
Dawson, I've done all the
research.

06:10.458 --> 06:11.875
The t21 is by far the best buy,

06:11.875 --> 06:13.209
and that's what we're getting.

06:13.209 --> 06:14.125
Yeah, well, in that case,

06:14.125 --> 06:15.750
I'd just prefer you didn't get
me a laptop.

06:15.750 --> 06:17.750
You need a laptop for school,
Dawson.

06:17.750 --> 06:19.209
I am getting you a laptop.

06:19.209 --> 06:19.917
Ok, dad, I appreciate you

06:19.917 --> 06:20.750
wanting to do this for me,

06:20.750 --> 06:21.708
but it's not fair if you only

06:21.708 --> 06:22.834
want to do it on your own terms.

06:22.834 --> 06:23.667
Not fair. A father wants to

06:23.667 --> 06:24.542
spend thousands of dollars

06:24.542 --> 06:26.083
on his son, and somehow it's
not fair.

06:26.083 --> 06:27.750
Why would you want to spend
thousands of dollars

06:27.750 --> 06:28.917
on something I don't even want?

06:28.917 --> 06:30.083
Because it's something you need.

06:30.083 --> 06:31.750
Look, it's practical. It's
functional.

06:31.750 --> 06:32.750
It'll last you for years.

06:32.750 --> 06:33.959
And it's not what I want.

06:33.959 --> 06:35.667
- Can I help you? - Yes, we'll
take the t21.

06:36.041 --> 06:37.375
Man: Ah, excellent choice.

06:37.375 --> 06:38.834
I'll bring that right out.

06:42.167 --> 06:43.167
Jack: Whoa.

06:43.333 --> 06:44.333
[SIGHS] We shouldn't have

06:44.333 --> 06:45.583
left her alone for an hour.

06:45.583 --> 06:47.959
That woman is an unstoppable
cleaning machine.

06:47.959 --> 06:49.875
Ooh, good. You're back.

06:50.167 --> 06:52.250
I'm just about to head out
myself.

06:52.250 --> 06:54.583
One last potluck at the ladies
auxiliary.

06:54.583 --> 06:55.583
Ah, ah, ah.

06:56.084 --> 06:57.084
Sorry.

06:57.542 --> 06:59.167
I assume you two have eaten

06:59.167 --> 07:00.959
your usual quota of junk food.

07:00.959 --> 07:02.125
Obviously. You've done quite

07:02.125 --> 07:03.125
a number on that fridge.

07:03.125 --> 07:04.125
There's no point in leaving

07:04.125 --> 07:05.167
things for the last minute.

07:05.167 --> 07:06.917
Yeah, but the movers don't come
till tomorrow.

07:07.333 --> 07:09.583
8 a.m., bright and early.

07:09.583 --> 07:11.208
Which means someone has her work

07:11.208 --> 07:13.333
cut out for her with that room
of hers.

07:13.917 --> 07:15.250
Especially if she still plans
to go

07:15.250 --> 07:16.750
to the movies tonight with
Dawson.

07:16.750 --> 07:19.291
Oh, I get it. Ok, this cheerful
disposition

07:19.291 --> 07:20.959
is just a passive-aggressive
attempt

07:20.959 --> 07:22.583
to get me to stay home tonight,
isn't it?

07:24.042 --> 07:26.167
Which, by the way, I gladly
will.

07:26.750 --> 07:28.041
Oh, don't be silly, dear.

07:28.041 --> 07:30.042
It's Dawson's last night. You
go out.

07:30.583 --> 07:31.792
Have fun.

07:31.792 --> 07:32.792
I know, but...

07:33.166 --> 07:35.167
I mean it is our last night in
this house.

07:36.083 --> 07:37.375
Maybe we should do something...

07:38.166 --> 07:40.166
Special, like commemorate the
occasion.

07:41.708 --> 07:44.042
Our last night in this rickety
old house

07:44.125 --> 07:45.458
with no pictures on the wall,

07:45.458 --> 07:46.750
no food in the fridge?

07:47.834 --> 07:49.000
Honestly, Jennifer,

07:49.750 --> 07:50.834
there's no point in being

07:50.834 --> 07:52.083
sentimental about these things.

07:53.208 --> 07:55.166
All right. I'll tell you what.

07:56.209 --> 07:57.291
You'll come home tonight,

07:57.291 --> 07:58.291
we'll have tea.

08:00.083 --> 08:01.166
You packed the kettle.

08:01.875 --> 08:03.125
Don't forget to wear a sweater.

08:03.125 --> 08:04.834
It's supposed to be chilly
tonight.

08:11.667 --> 08:14.000
Ahh. Let's get this baby set up.

08:14.000 --> 08:15.000
Later, dad.

08:15.000 --> 08:16.000
Hey.

08:16.166 --> 08:17.042
Hey.

08:17.042 --> 08:18.083
Are you a sight for sore eyes.

08:18.083 --> 08:19.084
You ready to go?

08:19.084 --> 08:20.291
- Yeah. - Mitch: Well, where
you going?

08:20.291 --> 08:21.792
I'm going to the movies with
Jack and Jen.

08:21.792 --> 08:23.000
I'll be back later.

08:23.000 --> 08:25.000
Dawson, it's your last night at
home.

08:25.792 --> 08:26.834
And?

08:28.583 --> 08:30.667
I thought we'd spend it
together as a family.

08:30.667 --> 08:31.667
And I thought I would spend

08:31.667 --> 08:32.707
some time with my friends.

08:35.000 --> 08:37.041
Listen, I don't want to
embarrass anybody here.

08:37.041 --> 08:39.041
I'm sorry, Joey, but I'd really
appreciate it.

08:39.041 --> 08:40.582
- If you'd stay for dinner. -
Mitch.

08:41.042 --> 08:42.083
Dad, I'll be home later.

08:42.083 --> 08:43.207
Well, let me understand this.

08:43.667 --> 08:45.209
You would rather go to the
movies

08:45.209 --> 08:47.000
than spend what little time you
have left

08:47.000 --> 08:48.542
with myself, your mother,

08:48.542 --> 08:50.125
and your little baby sister?

08:50.125 --> 08:51.917
That's not what I said, dad.
What is so criminal

08:51.917 --> 08:53.333
about wanting to hang out with
my friends?

08:53.333 --> 08:54.375
You've been hanging out with

08:54.375 --> 08:55.208
your friends all month.

08:55.208 --> 08:56.834
What is going on with you?

08:56.834 --> 08:59.291
Nothing. I'm just trying to
figure out

08:59.291 --> 09:01.834
when my son became so
insensitive.

09:02.583 --> 09:04.084
Probably about the same time

09:04.084 --> 09:05.375
you became so overbearing.

09:06.208 --> 09:08.000
[LAUGHING]

09:10.041 --> 09:11.083
You'll stay for dinner, then.

09:11.083 --> 09:12.708
- No. - No?

09:12.708 --> 09:13.750
No, dad.

09:13.750 --> 09:15.167
Look, I'm stressed out enough

09:15.167 --> 09:16.583
about moving 3,000 miles away

09:16.583 --> 09:17.917
without having to worry about

09:17.917 --> 09:19.083
how I'm letting you down, ok?

09:19.083 --> 09:21.417
I'm gonna go to the movies,
I'll be back later,

09:21.417 --> 09:22.625
and I'm not gonna feel guilty

09:22.625 --> 09:23.625
about wanting to spend

09:23.625 --> 09:25.042
some portion of my last night
here

09:25.042 --> 09:26.708
with the few people who mean
the world to me.

09:27.041 --> 09:28.083
Is that ok?

09:28.959 --> 09:30.083
Do what you want.

09:37.417 --> 09:38.041
Mom?

09:38.041 --> 09:39.625
Honey, go.

09:41.125 --> 09:42.625
Have a good time.

09:47.209 --> 09:49.000
Dawson, we don't have to go.

09:49.000 --> 09:51.667
No, let's get out of here. Come
on.

09:53.125 --> 09:56.417
